[1] Canada (British Columbia)
Date: 24 Mar 2014
Source: Vancouver Sun [edited]
http://www.vancouversun.com/health/Measles+cases+double+past+week/9655946/story.html


The number of measles cases in the Fraser Valley has doubled in the past week, reaching 228 confirmed cases as of Monday [24 Mar 2014], according to the Fraser Health Authority.

Despite the increase, the region's chief medical officer said he is encouraged that hundreds of unvaccinated individuals in the eastern Fraser Valley are coming in to local clinics, pharmacies and doctors' offices to get immunized.

"Despite more than 200 cases, we haven't seen much leakage into the general population," Dr. Paul Van Buynder said Monday [24 Mar 2014]. "At this point, the containment appears to be working around (the eastern Fraser Valley). We are seeing new cases within that community because people who didn't get it in the 1st wave are now getting it." Health officials in the region have been working with school, community and church groups to investigate the outbreak and set up control measures such as dedicated immunization clinics, Van Buynder said.

"If we manage to contain it, as we have so far, then I expect that we'll probably see another hundred or so cases within that community ... but not too much outside."

It is impossible to determine, however, whether members of the religious communities at the centre of the outbreak are now getting immunized, Van Buynder said, noting that people who receive immunizations are not asked about religious affiliation.

There have been no secondary infections linked to a case at Burnaby's BCIT campus, he added. The best protection against measles is 2 doses of the MMR vaccine. Van Buynder urged those who have not received the vaccine to get immunized immediately.

Anyone who is not vaccinated and suspects they have been exposed to measles or has developed symptoms should see a doctor, but notify the office beforehand in order to prevent the spread of the highly contagious disease. The Fraser Health Authority is offering vaccination clinics this week in Chilliwack and Mission.

[Byline: Tara Carman]

