[3] USA (California)
Date: 26 Mar 2014
Source: KABC Los Angeles News [edited]
http://abclocal.go.com/kabc/story?section=news/local/orange_county&id=9480590


Orange County health officials are warning residents of the biggest outbreak of measles in California.

This year [2014], 21 people in Orange County have been diagnosed with the highly contagious respiratory disease, and 7 have been hospitalized. In a typical year, Orange County has no reported cases of measles.

The Orange County Health Department held an emergency meeting Tuesday [25 Mar 2014] night to discuss the unexpected outbreak and encourage residents to get vaccinated. The vaccine is 99 percent effective after 2 doses.

Neighboring counties, such as Riverside and Los Angeles, have also seen a spike in cases.

