(1) Rostov
Date: 18 Mar 2014
Source: Rostov.aif.ru [in Russian, trans. Corr.VM, edited]
http://www.rostov.aif.ru/health/1126307


Since the beginning of this year [2014], 185 cases of measles have been recorded in the Rostov region, including 76 in January 2014, 81 in February 2014 and 22 cases in March 2014.

Half of the patients are children who attend kindergarten or school and who had not been vaccinated previously. Vaccination is low in gypsy [Roma, Romany] and [some] religious communities.

Measles has been recorded in 7 towns and 9 districts of the region.

------
(2) Kursk region
Date: 18 Mar 2014
Source: Remedium.ru [in Russian, trans. Corr.VM, edited]
http://remedium.ru/news/detail.php?ID=61146


New cases of measles in the Kursk region have not been detected for more than 3 weeks.

In total, 219 people contracted measles in the Kursk region, of which 212 are members of the Baptist community. The representatives of the communities of Baptists refused vaccination against measles and other infectious diseases for religious reasons.

According to Rospotrebnadzor, in 2013 in Russia, measles incidence has increased by 10.2 percent. 2300 cases of the disease were registered in total in 58 regions of the country.

